Text.string: Oh, thank you, dearie. I knew I could still count on the kindness of strangers, even in these times. Come talk to me at the homestead.
Oh, hi there, dearie! Couldja help out a neighbor?

Now you've un-borrowed all our spare parts, come on back to the homestead, dearie. I hate to be a bother to ya. Usually Pa's the one to settle up on these neighborly disagreements. He's just got a way with people.

You are too kind, dearie, returning those parts to us. If it ain't too much trouble, would you mind re-installin' 'em? My hip's been acting up ever since I tweaked it haulin' that reactor core up a flight of stairs.
Good fences make good neighbors, and electrified fences make well-behaved neighbors.
Power's back on! I was worried my custard would go bad right there in the icebox. And now the specimens won't come out of cryosleep. Anyway, sure is nice to have some help around here.
I am astonished by the kindness of strangers. I must insist on some payment. Come on over!
Homestead's seen better days... but if you can't take care of your home, and your antimatter containment chamber, and your family... what CAN you take care of? Thanks, dearie.

Those rascals from the festival “borrowed” spare parts from our homestead. Now, I don't mean to be a fussy neighbor, but we can't even keep the skags out or turn the lights on anymore! Pa usually takes care of this sort of thing, but he's out on chores. So could you be a dearie and go get the parts back from those rascals?
Sure. I'm always up to “chase down some rascals”.
Oh, I know how to take care of “rascals”. My fists, for starters.
If by “rascals” you mean “murderous vermin”, I'm in.
“Rascals”, are they? The thievin', murderin' sort of rascal, I assume.

Pa and I are simple folk. We settled out here on account of the isolation, rather'n despite it. Just honest people, working the honest land, building honest superconductors out in the shed. The way it's meant to be!
Oh, those rascals are usin' our fuse to power their nasty little radio tower! Make sure to ask 'em good and nicely. I'm sure they won't mind partin' with it.

Thanks, dearie. Radio's an awfully antiquated way to spread your message. Maybe now they'll splurge on somethin' with a little shine, like a hyperfiber Q3-ECHOline with whisper encryption. Gets the soaps like a snap!

It sounds like those rascals are usin' the core of our wind turbine as a bass amplifier for their little hootenanny! They won't mind if you take it back—I'm sure they could use a break from all their hootin' and hollerin' anyhow.

Thanks, dearie. You did them a favor, anyhow. Those bass drops are bad for the ol' eardrums. Might as well be doing the foxtrot inside the pressure wall of a Class-12 Skyshatter warhead, heh! No thankee!
